column1:
Pattern layout  for the Autotiles:

- Old Style : Autotiles from RPG Maker XP
- New Style: Autotiles from RPG Maker VX, ACE and MV
en:
Pattern layout  for the Autotiles:

- Old Style : Autotiles from RPG Maker XP
- New Style: Autotiles from RPG Maker VX, ACE and MV

column1:
Type of the Autotile:

-Floor: Autotiles used to draw grounds
- Wall: Autotiles used to draw walls
- Waterfall: Autotiles used to draw waterfalls
en:
Type of the Autotile:

-Floor: Autotiles used to draw grounds
- Wall: Autotiles used to draw walls
- Waterfall: Autotiles used to draw waterfalls

column1:
- [color=#FF0000]Left Click[/color]:
     Fit the image to the width and height of the canvas
- [color=#FF0000]CTRL + Left Click[/color]:
     Fit the image to the height of the canvas
- [color=#FF0000]ALT + Left Click[/color]:
     Fit the image to the width of the canvas
- [color=#FF0000]CTRL + Mouse Wheel in canvas[/color]:
     Mouse Wheel Up:          Zoom In
     Mouse Wheel Down:     Zoom Out
en:
- [color=#FF0000]Left Click[/color]:
     Fit the image to the width and height of the canvas
- [color=#FF0000]CTRL + Left Click[/color]:
     Fit the image to the height of the canvas
- [color=#FF0000]ALT + Left Click[/color]:
     Fit the image to the width of the canvas
- [color=#FF0000]CTRL + Mouse Wheel in canvas[/color]:
     Mouse Wheel Up:          Zoom In
     Mouse Wheel Down:     Zoom Out

column1:
Change the name, collision type, occlusion and animation speed of the selected tile.
You can [color=#FF0000]double-click[/color] on any item on the list to perform this same action
en:
Change the name, collision type, occlusion and animation speed of the selected tile.
You can [color=#FF0000]double-click[/color] on any item on the list to perform this same action
